article_text:
“The first Democratic presidential debate on Tuesday evening was an opportunity for the unknown challengers to Hillary Clinton to make an impression,” writes the Journal editorial board. “The four men on stage showed they lack the ability and will to take her on.” The editorial adds: “Unless Vice President Joe Biden joins the race, the Democratic Party’s Clinton coronation is back on schedule.”

A new study shows that ObamaCare harms the people it is supposed to help, notes the Journal. Wharton economists measured costs...
